      "sectionId": "dative-case",
      "title": "Dative Case",
      "tip": "The dative case answers кому? (to whom?) and чему? (to what?). Masculine nouns take -у/-ю, feminine nouns ending in -а take -е, and feminine nouns ending in -ь take -и.",
      "explanation": "The dative case (дательный падеж) marks the indirect object — the recipient of an action. It answers 'to whom?' (кому?) and 'to what?' (чему?). Masculine nouns take -у or -ю, feminine nouns ending in -а/-я take -е/-и, neuter nouns take -у/-ю. The dative is used with verbs like давать (to give), помогать (to help), звонить (to call).",
      "examples": [
        {
          "ru": "Я дал книгу брату.",
          "en": "I gave a book to my brother.",
          "highlight": "брату"
        },
        {
          "ru": "Скажи маме.",
          "en": "Tell mom.",
          "highlight": "маме"
        },
        {
          "ru": "Я помог другу.",
          "en": "I helped a friend.",
          "highlight": "другу"
        }
      ],
